HEADWORD: Logos
<hw>Log"os</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>lo`gos</grk> the word or form which expresses a thought, also, the
thought, fr. <?/ to speak.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A word; reason;
speech.</def> <rj><au>H. Bushell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The divine Word; Christ.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Logothete</ent>⟦br⟧
